<?page title="Fly Region" contentType="text/html;charset=UTF-8"?>
<zk>
	<window title="Fly Region" border="normal">
		<borderlayout height="500px">
			<center>
				<div>
					<button label="Go" onClick="east.open = !east.open" />
					The region appears at the wrong side and suddenly flies to the correct side when:
					<separator/>
					1. The region is not open when page loads;
					<separator/>
					2. It is set to open the first time.
					<separator/>
					* This happens in both Firefox and IE.
	* This applies to both East and South component (West and North work normally)
				</div>
			</center>
			<east id="east" size="200px" collapsible="true" open="false">
				<label value="east" />
			</east>
		</borderlayout>
	</window>
</zk>

